id: pm-kvev
title: "GH-495: extension context pm_root ignores root-layout trackers (falls back to non-existent .agents/pm)"
description: "Ancestor discovery in resolvePmRoot only recognized .agents/pm layouts, so bare invocations and the pm_root handed to extensions broke in root-layout workspaces."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 1
tags[5]: agent-ux,extensions,gh-issue,path-safety,sdk
created_at: "2026-07-10T11:07:07.017Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-10T11:32:37.318Z"
closed_at: "2026-07-10T11:32:37.317Z"
author: maintainer-agent
estimated_minutes: 60
acceptance_criteria: Bare pm invocations from inside a root-layout workspace resolve the tracker; extension command context pm_root equals the resolved root; pm --pm-path <ctx.pm_root> stats exits 0; unrelated ancestor settings.json without pm markers never hijacks resolution; regression tests cover discovery precedence (.agents/pm wins) and foreign/array/unparseable settings.json
risk: medium
confidence: high
severity: high
environment: "@unbrained/pm-cli 2026.7.10, root-layout tracker via pm init <dir>"
repro_steps: pm init <dir>; cd <dir>; pm create task t --ac a (fails tracker_not_initialized); extension command context.pm_root = <dir>/.agents/pm (non-existent)
resolution: "discoverPmRootFromAncestors now adopts <dir>/settings.json trackers (id_prefix/item_format marker required, .agents/pm precedence per level); explicit --path/PM_PATH semantics unchanged"
expected_result: Bare invocations and extension context pm_root resolve the tracker root the CLI actually uses in root-layout workspaces
actual_result: "Sandbox + integration probe: bare pm create/stats work from pm init <dir> workspaces; ctx.pm_root == workspace root; pm --pm-path <ctx.pm_root> stats exits 0; unrelated/array/unparseable ancestor settings.json ignored; fast suite 270/5510 and coverage gate 100/100/100/100 green"
dependencies[1]{id,kind,created_at,author,source_kind}:
