  node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/core/store/store-paths.spec.ts,project
close_reason: Root-layout ancestor discovery shipped with pm-marker hijack guard; extension pm_root context verified end-to-end
body: "GitHub: https://github.com/unbraind/pm-cli/issues/495\n\n## Root cause\ndiscoverPmRootFromAncestors (src/core/store/paths.ts) only probed <dir>/.agents/pm/settings.json while walking ancestors. Root-layout trackers (pm init <dir> writes settings.json directly into <dir> — the deliberate tracker-path mode kept by pm-x26a/GH-488) were invisible to implicit discovery. Every resolvePmRoot(cwd) call without --path/PM_PATH — including all extension context construction sites in src/cli/main.ts — fell back to <cwd>/.agents/pm, a non-existent directory. Worse than reported: even plain pm create failed from the workspace; GH-488's --pm-path-scoped follow-up hints were a bandage over this.\n\n## Fix\nAncestor discovery now also adopts <dir>/settings.json as a root-layout tracker, guarded by a pm-marker check (id_prefix or item_format present) so an unrelated tool's settings.json at an ancestor can never hijack resolution and receive pm writes. Per-level precedence keeps .agents/pm first. Explicit --path/PM_PATH behavior unchanged (carries user intent, no marker check).\n\n## Duplicate evidence\nExact all-status searches for GH-495, pm_root, and root-layout extension context returned no owning item; pm-x26a (GH-488, closed) owns init follow-up hint correctness only, not discovery."
